@Rich-Harris I tried experimenting with this on my Windows machine and the only way I succeeded to reliably get no errors in the tests was to lower the workers count (in the playwright config), and I guess the reason for it is that Windows is worse at dealing with CPU and RAM than the Linux/MacOS are. 
Recommended and the default amount of workers for playwright test is the half of the amount of CPU cores on the machine (source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/512a245f135e7c2430aebc698b65a299fe07dac6/packages/playwright-test/types/test.d.ts#L628 ) and the number of the CPU cores on the Github Actions Windows machines is 2 (source: https://docs.github.com/en/actions/using-github-hosted-runners/about-github-hosted-runners#supported-runners-and-hardware-resources ) 
I have a laptop with i5 processor with 4 CPU cores and 8GB of RAM (not bad, not great obviously) and still when I run the test with 8 workers I get error and the machine slows down a bit, so no wonder the Windows VM fails.
